body:
We have nightly build for python 3.8, so it should work. 
Please see [https://dev.azure.com/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/_build/results?buildId=111958](https://dev.azure.com/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/_build/results?buildId=111958)
Probably we should avoid linking to python libraries on Linux, in all the build configs.
is this a python lib that you built yourself? why is it finding static lib?
I saw the nightly build for python 3.8 is working fine. Yes I build python myself so maybe it is due to the way I build python.
It seems like you've missed `--enable-shared` option building the python
